title: Chelsea transfer news: Bayern Munich plot bid for Moussa Dembele | Metro News
text:
Louis Sealey for Metro.co.uk Sunday 19 Feb 2017 11:51 am Celtic’s Moussa Dembele has attracted attention from a host of clubs (Picture: Getty) 
Bayern Munich have entered the race to sign Chelsea and Arsenal target Moussa Dembele from Celtic, according to reports. 
The 20-year-old striker has been liked with a host of top European clubs after a scintillating run for the Scottish giants. Theo Walcott left red-faced as Arsenal fans slam club for 'disrespectful' gesture 
Dembele, who has scored 10 goals in his last eight games and 27 during the entire campaign, emerged as a target for Chelsea during the January transfer window. 
The Premier League leaders were believed to have made contact with Celtic over a possible move, but Brendan Rodgers reiterated the star was not for sale. 
Dembele will once again become the subject of intense speculation at the end of the season and the Daily Mirror say Bayern Munich will attempt to lure him to Germany. 
The Bundesliga outfit, who smashed Arsenal 5-1 in the Champions League last week, are reportedly readying a £30million move for the in-demand attacker. Chelsea fixtures
